{"parentUuid":"504ea1e9-4dac-473d-870b-33e0027b56e7","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/libnn","sessionId":"8f209af9-bc42-49a1-8f16-573eb6b02593","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"develop","agentId":"ad34d6728a38fe112","slug":"nested-forging-rabin","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W5cLM7vTyZkJv2WyHuDxmJ","type":"tool_result","content":"--- [1b35bf81] (score: 0.235) ---\n  Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_fast\n  Date: 2026-03-23\n  Outcome: improved\n  Speedup: 4.15x\n  Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_fast\n  Summary: Replaced ENA_TILING GEMM (vectorize col2=32, 12.5% VL util) with im2col + 4x2 GEMM using vd4dots (vectorize K=1152, ~100% VL util)\n  Approach: The ENA_TILING path used nn_mat_mul_kernel_tiling_q7 which vectorized across output channels (col2=32). At VLEN=1024/M2, only 32 of 256 possible elements were used per vector op (12.5% utilization). Replaced with the im2col + nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft path which uses 4x2 tiled GEMM with vd4dots vectorizing across the reduction dimension K=1152, achieving full VL utilization. Also eliminated the weight transpose step.\n\n--- [2afa80a1] (score: 0.231) ---\n  Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_fast\n  Date: 2026-03-23\n  Outcome: improved\n  Speedup: 1.043x (4.33x total from baseline 2292500)\n  Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_fast\n  Summary: Switched im2col from 2-pixel to 4-pixel batching with _unroll4 GEMM (4x4/M1) — 4.3% improvement over round 1\n  Approach: Changed buffer threshold from 2*K to 4*K and switched GEMM from nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft (4x2/M2) to _unroll4 (4x4/M1). Halves weight reloads, improves compute-to-load ratio from 1.33 to 2.0. Trade-off: M1 gives VL=128 instead of M2 VL=256, doubling inner loop iterations. Net effect: instruction count increased 13% but IPC improved 0.59->0.70, reducing cycles by 4.3%.\n\n--- [4f167833] (score: 0.222) ---\n  Function: riscv_nn_